div1.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT, WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
Ex Parte Charles M. Helmore, Petitioner. ORDER DENYING WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS. 3385L
This cuase coming on to be heard upon the petition of Charles M. Helmore for a writ of habeas corpus upon the matters and things set forth in the said petition, it is by the Court

ORDERED and ADJUDGED that the said petition be, and the same hereby is, denied and the said defendant petitioner Charles M. Helmore is hereby remanded to custody under process of this court, by which he is and has been held. Done in chabers this 19th day of July, 1916.
Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON. NORTHERN DIVISION.
Ex Parte Charles M. Helmore, Petitioner.
ORDER DENYING WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.
FILED IN THE U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, Northern Division JUL 21 1916 FRANK L. CROSBY, Cleark, By Deputy
